member.example:
So, to create a custom menu to insert pieces of HTML:
ToolbarMenu menu = new ToolbarMenu("custommenu");
ToolbarMenuItem item = new ToolbarMenuItem();
item.Name = "Choose me";
item.Value = "Inserted text";
menu.Items.Add(item);
item = new ToolbarMenuItem();
item.Name = "Another item";
item.Value = "More inserted text";
menu.Items.Add(item);
menu.Title="Test Menu";
menu.OnChange = "insertHtml";
richtextbox.CreateToolbarMenu(menu);
You then add the client-side script function to the page:
function insertHtml(editor,htmlmode,text,value)
{
	editor.focus();
	sel = editor.document.selection.createRange();
	sel.pasteHTML(value); 
}

For more information on working with the Document Object Model in Internet Explorer and manipulating the document in the iframe,
see MSDN.
